11: Am I headed in the right direction?!
17:
I didn't know a vehicle capable of
traveling over snow with such speed
existed...
21:
Yeah, snowmobiles are the best!
Although this one is MUCH better
than the ones from my world!
34:
Urk... M-Marina, I implore you... The
swerving... make it stop...
40:
Wow... This place is huge. I guess
that makes sense for your
kingdom's library.
44:
Originally, this place belonged to a
woman named Luceltia. It has quite
the history.
47:
That being said, I've only been able
to come here recently myself. We
were always on the run, after all.
52:
I, for one, am surprised you wished
to come here, Marina.
57:
What, didn't take me for a
bookworm? I CAN read, you know.
60:
Although I will admit I mostly read
pulp fiction-y adventure and
mystery novels.
66:
I'm the same way. When I was
young, I used to secretly read
romance novels under the covers.
74:
I read those too... I wanted to show
off in front of Shakari.
78:
Gotcha. In any case, we're not here
to find a book for me.
81:
Ah, here we go. Looks like there's a
whole section on the Champions.
86:
You wish to know more of the
legends of our world? Why not
simply ask me?
89:
...Besides, it's not like the legends
have much substance to them...
94: True. The stories are all the same.
96:
Evil appears, and a Champion is
chosen to wield the power of light.
It's happened time and time again.
100:
But what happened after "happily
ever after"? They don't really talk
about that, do they?
104:
I always assumed that many of
them did not return from their
quest...
108:
Well... Maybe they live long, boring
lives, and the author just didn't see
fit to write it down.
113:
What will you do with this
knowledge? It seems like it will only
bring more pain.
117:
Maybe, but... what if there's one or
two Champions that DIDN'T meet a
tragic end?
124:
You've seen that torn-up book in the
Starview Village library, right?
126:
Stella told me it was left by the
Champion Claire.
133:
How strange... I have no recollection
of such a Champion.
136:
And I don't see that name anywhere
on the shelf.
141:
Huh? But he vanquished evil and all
that junk too! How could they leave
Claire out?
150:
Ah! The Amorous Clarence's debut
work!
155:
You won't find it on that shelf... It
should beAh, here!
158:
Clarence was an accomplished
writer, penning everything from
picture books to stage plays! I too
read his books as a child.
160:
HIs debut work, "The Adventures of
Claire," is about a young man who
falls in love with a fairy princess
incapable of smiling...
162:
If I recall correctly... In the end, Claire
granted the princess' wish without
using his sword...
166:
Gotcha... Then that must be the
book I'm looking for.
178:
That was all a dream, remember?
The real Claire didn't do that.
181:
You know, this Clarence guy seems
like he had a pretty good life. LOTS of
lovers and secret love children.
183:
That's, uh, not exactly good, but it
seems like he had a thrilling life.
191:
Hey, do you know when your
birthday is, Stella?
195:
You don't, do you? Well... Happy
birthday! Consider this a belated
birthday gift.
203: Thank you... I will treasure it.
207:
You know, I DO think Marina is
pretty...
214:
But more importantly, she's also
cool. She makes you want to be
more like her.
218: Yeah, I know what you mean.
222:
Say, Amelia, I've got an idea. Could I
get your help with it?
242:
We looked all over for these. Here's
today's haul!
246:
Are these... picture books? From
Japan?
249:
You don't think I've gone soft now, do
you?
254:
So what if you have? You can cry
too, Czarina.
258:
Oh, by the way, I really like this one!
The one about the wardrobe that
turns into a tunnel!
262:
I like the one about the pink ghosts
that change shape.
